ords/java&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Aspose.Words for Java&lt;/a&gt; to develop Word Processing applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aspose.Words for Java provides the easiest mechanism to create, edit &amp;amp; convert Microsoft Word documents without requiring Microsoft Office. A few of the worth mentioning features of Aspose.Words for Java are as follows. If you wish to further dig in, please check out the &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.aspose.com/words/java/developer-guide/&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;Developer&#039;s Guide&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Import and export with 35+ supported file formats.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Programmatic access to the properties of all document elements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Split a document into parts, merge several documents or compare two documents to find out differences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High fidelity rendering of document pages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate reports with Mail Merge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;LINQ Reporting Engine.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Aspose.Words Java (Maven) for Eclipse&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aspose.Words Maven Project (Wizard)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Creates Maven project to use Aspose.Words for Java. Please follow New -&amp;gt; Project -&amp;gt; Maven-&amp;gt; Aspose.Words Maven Project.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Aspose.Words Code Example (Wizard)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Lets you copy the downloaded Code Examples into your project. Please follow New -&amp;gt; Other -&amp;gt; Java -&amp;gt; Aspose.Words Code Example&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;NOTE: Selected Code Examples will be copied under &quot;com.aspose.words.examples&quot; package, whereas the resources needed to run examples will be copied to the corresponding directory within &quot;src/main/resources&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other Features&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Supports Eclipse Mars.1 (4.5.1) and later&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compatible with Mac, Linux Flavors and Windows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Native IDE user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open Source&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Code Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Aspose.Words Code Example wizard currently integrates the following Aspose.Words examples with the Eclipse IDE&lt;/p&gt;
